    caption: [Mechanism of gene regulation by the transcription fac- tor FOXO1. Insulin activates the signaling cascade shown in Figure 12–16, leading to activation of protein kinase B (PKB). FOXO1 in the cytosol is phosphorylated by PKB, and the phosphorylated transcription factor is tagged by the attachment of ubiquitin for degradation by prote- asomes. FOXO1 that remains unphosphorylated or is dephosphorylated can enter the nucleus, bind to a response element, and trigger transcrip- tion of the associated genes. Insulin therefore has the effect of turning off the expression of these genes, which include PEP carboxykinase and glucose 6-phosphatase.],
