    caption: [Removal of a glucose residue from the nonreducing end of a glycogen chain by glycogen phosphorylase. This process is repetitive; the enzyme removes successive glu- cose residues until it reaches the fourth glucose unit from a branch point (see Fig. 15–28). c15PrinciolesOfMetabolicRegulation.indd Page 614 17/09/12 1:24 PM user-F408 c15PrinciolesOfMetabolicRegulation.indd Page 614 17/09/12 1:24 PM user-F408 /Users/user-F408/Desktop /Users/user-F408/Desktop 614],
